verbose_text: However, circulating MSCs preferentially migrate, extravasate at the lesion vicinity, and accumulate at sites of tissue damage and inflammation; this is in response to chemoattractants particularly stromal cell derived factor 1 (SDF-1) which interacts with the CXCR4 receptor expressed on MSC [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR] and is referred to systemic homing [XREF_BIBR].
